==English==

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|grc|πολύ||many}} + {{m|grc|γυνή||woman, wife}}; synchronically, {{affix|en|poly-|-gyny}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/pəˈlɪdʒɪnɪ/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~|polygynies}}

# The state or practice of having several [[wife|wives]] at the same time; [[plurality]] of wives; marriage to several wives.
#: {{cite-book|title={{w|The Principles of Sociology}} |author={{w|Herbert Spencer}} |year=1883 |page=685 |passage=We may infer that in most cases where '''polygyny''' exists, monogamy co-exists to a greater extent, and in all other cases to a considerable extent.}}
# The condition of an [[ant]] [[colony]] that has multiple egg-laying [[queen]]s.

